Create a Salesforce DX Project

1) In Visual Studio Code, open the Command Palette by pressing Cmd+Shift+P
2) Type SFDX.
3) Select SFDX: Create Project.
4) Press Enter to accept the standard option.
5) Enter HelloWorldLightningWebComponent as the project name and Press Enter.
6) Select a folder to store the project.
7) Click Create Project.

Authorize Your Trailhead Playground
1) Open the Command Palette Cmd+Shift+P
2) Type SFDX.
3) Select SFDX: Authorize an Org.
4) Press Enter to accept the Project Default login URL option.
5) Press Enter to accept the default alias. This opens the Salesforce login in a separate browser window.
6) Log in using your Trailhead Playground credentials.
7) If prompted to allow access, click Allow.

Create a Lightning Web Component
1) Open the Command Palette Cmd+Shift+P
2) Type SFDX.
3) Select SFDX: Create Lightning Web Component
4) Enter helloWorld for the name of the new component.
5) Press Enter to accept the default force-app/main/default/lwc.
6) Press Enter.
7) Add code to the JS, HTML and XML files

Deploy to Your Trailhead Playground
1) Right-click the default folder under force-app/main.
2) Click in "Deploy source to org"

Add Component to App in Lightning Experience
1) Open the Command Palette Cmd+Shift+P
2) Type SFDX.
3) Select SFDX: Open Default Org.
4) This opens your Trailhead Playground in a separate browser.
5) From the App Launcher, find and select Sales.
6) Click Setup gear then select Edit Page.
7) Drag the helloWorld Lightning web component from the Custom area of the Lightning Components list to the top of the Page Canvas.
8) Click Save.
9) Click Activate.
10) Click Assign as Org Default.
11) Click Save.
12) Click Save again, then click Back arrow to return to the page.
Refresh the page to view your new component.